Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle at neck join. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie draw three such stamps (EES XVII p.80, 37, 116, 13 and 200, 20). Name Eukleitos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0350.10.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0947)
